description: Borrowed from Middle French psychogonie, from Late Latin psychogonia, from Koine Greek ψυχογονία (psukhogonía), from ψυχή (psukhḗ, “soul, mind”) + γόνος (gónos, “descent”). By surface analysis, psycho- +‎ -gony.

entries.meaning: (philosophy) The study of the origins and development of the soul or mind.
